🧬 Shared invariants (important)

These are what allow mass bonding like you said.

Examples:
	•	basic fairness expectations
	•	shared ranking baselines
	•	common reference points (“top items,” “consensus picks”)
	•	interpretable clusters

Without this:
→ system fragments
With too much:
→ system becomes rigid

So you want:

soft invariants, not hard uniformity

⸻

⚠️ Failure modes to design against

1. Noise flood (pure democracy failure)

→ low-quality signals dominate

2. Elite lock (meritocracy failure)

→ system stops adapting

3. Wealth capture (market failure)

→ power concentrates

4. Fragmentation (over-personalization)

→ no shared reality

5. Monoculture (single model dominance)

→ brittle collapse

